EventItemTitle: Report of the Committee on Housing and Buildings

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Introduction be Approved by Council approved by Roll Call.
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to extending the rent stabilization laws.
EventItemMatterName: Extending the rent stabilization laws.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation that would create a review process for Individual Apartments Improvement rent increases and  make such increases a temporary surcharge rather than a permanent rent increase.
EventItemMatterName: Create a review process for Individual Apartments Improvement rent increases and  make such increases a temporary surcharge rather than a permanent rent increase.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to approve, A.1865, in relation to repealing vacancy decontrol.
EventItemMatterName: Repealing vacancy decontrol. (A.1865)

EventItemTitle: Resolution determining that a public emergency requiring rent control in the City of New York continues to exist and will continue to exist on and after April 1, 2015.
EventItemMatterName: Determining that a public emergency requiring rent control in the City of New York continues to exist and will continue to exist on and after April 1, 2015.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation that would end deregulation of rent regulated apartments.
EventItemMatterName: End deregulation of rent regulated apartments.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign S.951, which repeals provisions of the Emergency Tenant Protection Act of 1974 that allow a 20 percent rent increase bonus after the vacancy of a tenant in a rent stabilized unit.
EventItemMatterName: Repeals provisions of the Emergency Tenant Protection Act of 1974 that allow a 20 percent rent increase bonus after the vacancy of a tenant in a rent stabilized unit. (S.951)

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign S.2830,  legislation amending the administrative code of the city of New York, the Emergency Tenant Protection Act of 1974 and the Emergency Housing Rent Control Law, in relation to making the Major Capital Improvement (MCI) rent increase a temporary surcharge.
EventItemMatterName: Emergency Tenant Protection Act of 1974 and the Emergency Housing Rent Control Law, in relation to making the Major Capital Improvement (MCI) rent increase a temporary surcharge. (S.2830)

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.398, which will provide rent control tenants relief from high rent increases.
EventItemMatterName: Provide rent control tenants relief from high rent increases.  (A.398)

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign S.2828/A.3809, which prohibits property owners from adjusting the preferential rent amount upon the renewal of a lease for a rent stabilized unit.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibits property owners from adjusting the preferential rent amount upon the renewal of a lease for a rent stabilized unit. (S.2828/A.3809)

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A. 344 in relation to Mitchell-Lama and Project-Based Section 8 developments.
EventItemMatterName: Mitchell-Lama and Project-Based Section 8 developments. (A.344)

EventItemMatterName: Requiring the development of a guide for building owners regarding aging in place.

EventItemMatterName: Grant NYC the authority to enforce State worker protection laws.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation granting New York City the authority to set its own minimum wage.
EventItemMatterName: Granting NYC the authority to set its own minimum wage.

EventItemMatterName: Requiring a survey and study of racial, ethnic and gender diversity among the directors, officers and executive level staff members of city contractors.

EventItemMatterName: Racial diversity in the leadership of city contractors.

EventItemMatterName: Requiring the commissioner of the department of correction to post a quarterly report regarding the visitation of incarcerated individuals.

EventItemMatterName: Prohibit discrimination on the basis of gender expression or identity. (A.4558B/S.61B)

EventItemMatterName: Declaring the practice of “curative therapy,” also known as “reparative” or “conversion” therapy, or any attempt to change, alter, or “correct” a person’s sexual orientation, to be unethical.

EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to conduct community air quality surveys and publish the results annually.
